      "writtenOn": "2019-02-07T22:19:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Image handling is different than path handling. In general glyphs always have mask, but may not have a path. A bitmap font is an example of this situation. If the glyph is not empty (has a width and height \u003e 0), then it will always have an image (even thought some of the code is written like it wont). The code needs to cache the image and path information to handle the corner case when the code process glyphs as masks, but one of the glyphs is too large to fit in the atlas. This corner case force the code to have a functioning getGlyphMetrics. Also, a functioning getGlyphMetrics is needed to share code. This is why hasImage is not similar to hasPath. Also, I think that hasPath and hasImage may need to be renamed to be clearer. hasImage does not need to calculate the image because serialize will call findImage which is guaranteed to produce an image if w \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 h\u003e 0.\n\nThe big picture is to have SkRemoteGlyphCache and GPU use the same strike lookup code. This change simplifies combining the two code paths. \n\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/184803 is a working prototype of the combined code for the Mask case.\n\nI\u0027m trying to break up that prototype into small careful CLs.",
